oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Ensign James Carmichael Greer
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Ensign James Carmichael Greer was from Loudon, Tennessee and was the brother of Lt. John Barksdale Greer. He was commissioned November 9, 1918 in the United States Navy. He later served on Gov. Frank Clements staff. He also served as the commander of American Legion Post 120 in Loudon. He died in 1954.
